Petrobras to Invest $4 Billion in Drilling in 2011, O Globo Says

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-02-12T14:00:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-12/petrobras-to-invest-4-billion-in-drilling-in-2011-o-globo-says.html
  Petroleo Brasileiro SA  plans to
invest $4 billion to boost drilling by 24 percent this year,  O
Globo  said, citing Jeferson Kinzel, the company’s general
manager for exploratory projects.  Petrobras plans to drill 162 wells, of which 53 will be
offshore and 109 onshore, up from 130 in 2010, the Rio de
Janeiro-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helder Marinho in São Paulo at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Francisco Marcelino at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net . 